<record xmlns='http://www.loc.gov/MARC21/slim'><leader>02794cam a22005052u 4500</leader><controlfield tag='001'>5474602</controlfield><controlfield tag='005'>20181017112721.0</controlfield><controlfield tag='007'>he u||024||||</controlfield><controlfield tag='008'>080220s1985    xxu ||| b     ||| | eng d</controlfield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='035'><subfield code='9'>(ericd)ED277368</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='037'><subfield code='a'>ED277368</subfield><subfield code='b'>ERIC</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='040'><subfield code='a'>ericd</subfield><subfield code='b'>eng</subfield><subfield code='c'>ericd</subfield><subfield code='d'>MvI</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='091'><subfield code='a'>mfm</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='1' ind2=' ' tag='100'><subfield code='a'>Johnson, Debra Wilcox.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='1' ind2='0' tag='245'><subfield code='a'>Literacy and Libraries</subfield><subfield code='h'>[microform] :</subfield><subfield code='b'>A Planning Manual /</subfield><subfield code='c'>Debra Wilcox Johnson and Jennifer A. Soule.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='260'><subfield code='a'>[Washington, D.C.] :</subfield><subfield code='b'>Distributed by ERIC Clearinghouse,</subfield><subfield code='c'>1985.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='300'><subfield code='a'>84 p.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Sponsoring Agency: Illinois State Library, Springfield.</subfield><subfield code='5'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='520'><subfield code='a'>Designed to help librarians and trustees make informed planning decisions concerning the development or improvement of library literacy services, this manual discusses the following topics: (1) the problem of illiteracy; (2) identifying adult new learners; (3) providers of literacy services; (4) the library&apos;s role in literacy activities; (5) cooperation with other providers of literacy services; (6) the community role; (7) making the decision to participate in literacy activities; (8) target groups for literacy services; (9) setting goals and objectives; (10) the availability of resources; (11) evaluating the literacy project; (12) publicizing library services; and (13) materials selection. Suggestions for further reading are provided for most topics. Five appendices include a selected list of publishers of adult education materials, a planning checklist, a sample needs assessment survey, a sample evaluation survey, and a levels of materials chart. (KM)</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='521'><subfield code='a'>Media Staff.</subfield><subfield code='b'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='521'><subfield code='a'>Practitioners.</subfield><subfield code='b'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='530'><subfield code='a'>May also be available online. Address as at 14/8/18: </subfield><subfield code='u'>https://eric.ed.gov/</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='533'><subfield code='a'>Microfiche.</subfield><subfield code='b'>[Washington D.C.]:</subfield><subfield code='c'>ERIC Clearinghouse</subfield><subfield code='e'>microfiches : positive.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='7' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Adult Education.</subfield><subfield code='2'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='1' ind2='7' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Adult Literacy.</subfield><subfield code='2'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='7' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Community Attitudes.</subfield><subfield code='2'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='7' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Community Support.</subfield><subfield code='2'>ericd</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='7' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Financial Support.</subfield><subfi